<div><div><h2>GAIL (India) second-quarter profit jumps 50 percent, tops estimates</h2></div><div>(reuters) - state-run gas utility gail (india) ltd posted a 50 percent jump in second-quarter profit on monday boosted by higher revenue from its natural gas marketing business. profit came in at 19.63 billion rupees ($268.86 million) for the three months ended sept. 30 compared with 13.10 billion rupees a year earlier the company said bit.ly/2zoe4li. analysts on average had expected a profit of 15.31 billion rupees according to refinitiv data. revenue from operations jumped 55.3 percent to 192.75 billion rupees. ($1 = 73.0125 indian rupees) all quotes delayed a minimum of 15 minutes. see here for a complete list of exchanges and delays.   2018 reuters. all rights reserved.</div></div>